The paper discusses recent developments in deep reinforcement learning, specifically in the context of multi-agent environments. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on coordination and decision-making among multiple agents, indicating that it may also belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. The paper also discusses modifications to the training procedure and communication among agents, which suggests that it may belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.MA, cs.RO, and cs.SY.
